1
00:00:12,250 --> 00:00:18,460
[2009]

2
00:00:24,830 --> 00:00:25,480
Chuan,

3
00:00:27,070 --> 00:00:28,600
I want to ask you a question.

4
00:00:29,760 --> 00:00:30,640
Tell me...

5
00:00:33,070 --> 00:00:34,600
What's the scariest thing?

6
00:00:35,260 --> 00:00:38,430
Your feet stinking up the place every day
is scary enough.

7
00:00:38,430 --> 00:00:39,090
Be serious.

8
00:00:41,310 --> 00:00:42,780
Mice, snakes.

9
00:00:43,320 --> 00:00:44,240
Not that kind.

10
00:00:46,630 --> 00:00:48,560
What's the most terrifying thing?

11
00:00:50,030 --> 00:00:50,750
Death?

12
00:00:52,430 --> 00:00:53,550
Not that either.

13
00:00:54,240 --> 00:00:55,320
Let me rephrase it.

14
00:00:56,670 --> 00:00:57,880
Hypothetically—

15
00:00:58,000 --> 00:00:59,640
let's say a person's whole life

16
00:00:59,640 --> 00:01:01,000
has already

17
00:01:01,000 --> 00:01:02,000
been written out.

18
00:01:02,200 --> 00:01:03,280
It's already set.

19
00:01:04,510 --> 00:01:07,770
And you could know in advance
what's going to happen to you.

20
00:01:07,870 --> 00:01:09,070
Would you want to know

21
00:01:09,710 --> 00:01:10,560
or not?

22
00:01:13,230 --> 00:01:14,840
Hey, is there anything wrong
with your brain?

23
00:01:14,840 --> 00:01:16,280
How could it be set?

24
00:01:16,360 --> 00:01:18,050
Hypothetically.

25
00:01:22,120 --> 00:01:22,950
I wouldn't want to know.

26
00:01:22,950 --> 00:01:24,400
It wouldn't be fun anymore.

27
00:01:24,400 --> 00:01:25,200
Why?

28
00:01:25,680 --> 00:01:27,190
If you could know,

29
00:01:27,430 --> 00:01:28,280
you'd know

30
00:01:29,070 --> 00:01:30,840
what bad things are going to happen.

31
00:01:30,840 --> 00:01:32,300
and avoid them in advance.

32
00:01:32,350 --> 00:01:33,150
Isn't that good?

33
00:01:33,150 --> 00:01:34,880
Alright, then I'd want to know.

34
00:01:35,150 --> 00:01:36,150
Wait, that's not right.

35
00:01:36,150 --> 00:01:37,680
Didn't you say it's already set?

36
00:01:37,680 --> 00:01:39,080
Then how could I avoid it?

37
00:01:39,400 --> 00:01:41,070
Like in those

38
00:01:41,120 --> 00:01:42,650
time-traveling TV series,

39
00:01:42,940 --> 00:01:45,070
they already knew what was going to happen

40
00:01:45,070 --> 00:01:47,039
and tried their best to change it,

41
00:01:47,070 --> 00:01:49,000
but the outcome was still the same.

42
00:01:49,530 --> 00:01:50,590
It hasn't changed.

43
00:01:50,780 --> 00:01:52,870
You can't change anything. It's pointless.

44
00:01:52,870 --> 00:01:53,729
What about you?

45
00:01:54,070 --> 00:01:57,070
Would you want to know or not?

46
00:01:59,590 --> 00:02:01,070
What kind of stuff have you been reading?

47
00:02:01,070 --> 00:02:02,480
Mystery novels.

48
00:02:05,430 --> 00:02:06,040
Chuan,

49
00:02:07,760 --> 00:02:08,800
I just feel

50
00:02:08,800 --> 00:02:09,870
that people

51
00:02:10,310 --> 00:02:11,640
are too insignificant.

52
00:02:12,120 --> 00:02:13,120
They know nothing

53
00:02:14,400 --> 00:02:16,060
and can't see the big picture.

54
00:02:16,520 --> 00:02:17,280
All they can see is

55
00:02:17,280 --> 00:02:20,140
what exists within their own
limited perspective.

56
00:02:20,400 --> 00:02:23,200
So sometimes,
it's really scary to think about it.

57
00:02:23,710 --> 00:02:25,120
It's like fate

58
00:02:25,120 --> 00:02:26,320
has blindfolded you.

59
00:02:28,000 --> 00:02:29,760
Real life is the same.

60
00:02:29,960 --> 00:02:31,290
Every day is uncertain.

61
00:02:32,710 --> 00:02:35,310
So I know
what the most terrifying thing is now.

62
00:02:35,360 --> 00:02:37,020
The unpredictability of life

63
00:02:37,150 --> 00:02:38,810
is the most terrifying thing.

64
00:02:43,520 --> 00:02:44,150
What?

65
00:02:45,630 --> 00:02:46,280
Sis,

66
00:02:46,900 --> 00:02:47,900
I realize you

67
00:02:48,790 --> 00:02:49,590
have grown up.

68
00:02:50,630 --> 00:02:51,750
I just hope

69
00:02:52,150 --> 00:02:54,400
that my life will be smooth and easy,

70
00:02:54,750 --> 00:02:56,630
like a straight, steady river,

71
00:02:57,030 --> 00:02:58,470
without wind or waves,

72
00:02:58,870 --> 00:03:01,000
smooth and steady all the way.

73
00:03:03,770 --> 00:03:05,770
Life is hard—that's normal.

74
00:03:06,630 --> 00:03:08,490
Nothing is certain in this world.

75
00:03:09,000 --> 00:03:10,060
Live in the moment.

76
00:03:10,690 --> 00:03:12,010
What you feel right now

77
00:03:12,080 --> 00:03:13,080
matters most.

78
00:03:16,470 --> 00:03:18,000
Alright, stop overthinking.

79
00:03:18,000 --> 00:03:19,530
I'll always be here for you.

80
00:03:20,030 --> 00:03:20,560
Here,

81
00:03:20,750 --> 00:03:21,400
read it.

82
00:03:22,360 --> 00:03:23,360
Okay!

83
00:03:26,310 --> 00:03:27,640
Life is unpredictable.

84
00:03:29,280 --> 00:03:30,430
Live in the moment.

85
00:03:33,870 --> 00:03:36,000
I trust what I'm feeling right now.

86
00:03:38,620 --> 00:03:39,680
Let's get married.

87
00:03:41,710 --> 00:03:42,520
Okay.

88
00:03:43,470 --> 00:03:44,530
Let's get married.

89
00:05:03,960 --> 00:05:09,720
[Sunsets Secrets Regrets]

90
00:05:10,130 --> 00:05:12,470
[Episode 13]

91
00:05:44,110 --> 00:05:45,240
Jiang Cheng, right?

92
00:05:46,230 --> 00:05:47,360
The game now begins.

93
00:05:57,750 --> 00:05:58,720
Cheng.

94
00:06:01,750 --> 00:06:02,880
What does this mean?

95
00:06:03,480 --> 00:06:05,460
You can't bring dangerous items
to meet Old Scorpion.

96
00:06:05,460 --> 00:06:06,660
Old Scorpion is here?

97
00:06:10,120 --> 00:06:11,920
You're not Old Scorpion, right?

98
00:06:14,480 --> 00:06:15,480
What do you think?

99
00:06:21,330 --> 00:06:23,130
You took our phones when we left,

100
00:06:23,240 --> 00:06:24,680
and now you're searching us.
What's this supposed to mean?

101
00:06:24,680 --> 00:06:25,360
Dahua.

102
00:06:25,480 --> 00:06:26,360
Shut up.

103
00:06:36,159 --> 00:06:37,560
You're taking this, too?

104
00:06:42,360 --> 00:06:43,159
It's okay now.

105
00:06:44,159 --> 00:06:44,730
Let's go.

106
00:07:06,430 --> 00:07:07,070
Hold on.

107
00:07:09,800 --> 00:07:10,800
What's your name?

108
00:07:10,950 --> 00:07:11,720
Jiang Cheng.

109
00:07:12,480 --> 00:07:13,600
I heard from Mr. He

110
00:07:13,720 --> 00:07:15,120
that you used to be a cop.

111
00:07:15,600 --> 00:07:16,190
Yeah.

112
00:07:16,800 --> 00:07:18,680
Before he sent you here,

113
00:07:18,920 --> 00:07:20,360
did he tell you

114
00:07:20,800 --> 00:07:22,930
that Old Scorpion hates cops the most?

115
00:07:39,510 --> 00:07:40,270
Is it fun?

116
00:07:40,800 --> 00:07:41,510
Not bad.

117
00:07:43,120 --> 00:07:44,680
Looks like Mr. He

118
00:07:44,870 --> 00:07:47,240
finally has someone with guts under him.

119
00:07:48,510 --> 00:07:50,500
I remember his cousin,

120
00:07:50,600 --> 00:07:51,310
Lai San—

121
00:07:51,630 --> 00:07:53,090
Before I even fired a shot,

122
00:07:53,720 --> 00:07:56,270
he pissed himself on the spot.

123
00:07:56,720 --> 00:07:58,190
Until now, I still can't forget

124
00:07:58,190 --> 00:07:59,560
the stench on him.

125
00:08:02,000 --> 00:08:03,130
I'm no match for you.

126
00:08:03,190 --> 00:08:04,390
I give up, Godfather.

127
00:08:05,510 --> 00:08:07,570
Do you know how to play Chinese chess?

128
00:08:09,600 --> 00:08:10,600
Let him come over.

129
00:08:11,990 --> 00:08:12,570
Come.

130
00:08:28,920 --> 00:08:29,430
Sit.

131
00:08:41,030 --> 00:08:41,960
Red moves first.

132
00:08:49,440 --> 00:08:50,550
I heard

133
00:08:51,150 --> 00:08:53,210
you've been in the limelight lately.

134
00:08:54,010 --> 00:08:56,010
The bosses gave me the opportunity.

135
00:08:58,840 --> 00:09:00,370
Why did you stop being a cop?

136
00:09:00,600 --> 00:09:02,720
I got in the way of someone's promotion

137
00:09:02,720 --> 00:09:03,520
and got set up.

138
00:09:08,670 --> 00:09:10,000
It's not really a secret.

139
00:09:10,000 --> 00:09:11,130
It was a badger game.

140
00:09:11,390 --> 00:09:12,510
During the investigation,

141
00:09:12,510 --> 00:09:14,240
a bag of white powder was found on me.

142
00:09:14,240 --> 00:09:15,870
Not only was I kicked
out of the police force,

143
00:09:15,870 --> 00:09:18,270
but I also did 3 years
in prison for nothing.

144
00:09:19,000 --> 00:09:20,460
You were framed by others.

145
00:09:20,840 --> 00:09:23,790
You were forced onto this path.

146
00:09:24,720 --> 00:09:25,780
Just for the money.

147
00:09:41,660 --> 00:09:43,260
Have you ever killed anyone?

148
00:09:48,790 --> 00:09:50,250
Have you ever killed a cop?

149
00:09:53,670 --> 00:09:54,930
I've heard about this.

150
00:09:55,360 --> 00:09:56,960
Cops who fall into your hands

151
00:09:57,000 --> 00:09:57,860
have no way out.

152
00:10:01,000 --> 00:10:02,440
I mean you.

153
00:10:04,550 --> 00:10:05,960
Seems like you haven't.

154
00:10:07,630 --> 00:10:08,750
I'm just a nobody.

155
00:10:09,270 --> 00:10:10,870
I'm nowhere near your level.

156
00:10:12,630 --> 00:10:14,510
But I think sometimes

157
00:10:14,510 --> 00:10:17,310
a living person is much more useful
than a dead one.

158
00:10:17,320 --> 00:10:18,870
I work for Mr. He.

159
00:10:19,610 --> 00:10:21,240
Sometimes, an extra friendship

160
00:10:21,240 --> 00:10:23,510
means another way to make money.

161
00:10:24,390 --> 00:10:26,630
To carry weight on both sides of the law,

162
00:10:27,080 --> 00:10:28,670
you can't just rely on being ruthless.

163
00:10:28,670 --> 00:10:29,800
You also need to have

164
00:10:30,750 --> 00:10:32,610
the capacity to tolerate others.

165
00:10:32,670 --> 00:10:33,670
What do you think?

166
00:10:41,320 --> 00:10:42,920
Are you telling me what to do?

167
00:10:43,330 --> 00:10:44,730
I didn't mean that at all.

168
00:10:57,440 --> 00:10:58,240
Good.

169
00:10:59,910 --> 00:11:00,720
Good.

170
00:11:01,550 --> 00:11:02,360
Good.

171
00:11:06,150 --> 00:11:08,280
I need someone like you working for me.

172
00:11:10,000 --> 00:11:11,440
What do you want me

173
00:11:11,540 --> 00:11:12,770
to do for you?

174
00:11:30,840 --> 00:11:31,870
Kill this man,

175
00:11:36,200 --> 00:11:38,150
and I'll give you a bright future.

176
00:11:52,550 --> 00:11:53,630
Position 2 is confirmed.

177
00:11:53,630 --> 00:11:55,490
They are unloading goods inside.

178
00:11:55,550 --> 00:11:56,200
Copy that.

179
00:11:57,150 --> 00:11:57,810
Leader Yao.

180
00:12:09,030 --> 00:12:10,430
Where is the backup team?

181
00:12:10,600 --> 00:12:12,660
SWAT will reach the pier in 5 minutes.

182
00:12:13,600 --> 00:12:15,360
What is He Wu doing? Where is he going?

183
00:12:15,360 --> 00:12:16,030
We tracked him

184
00:12:16,030 --> 00:12:17,320
near an abandoned factory.

185
00:12:17,320 --> 00:12:19,030
It's the opposite direction from Jingang.

186
00:12:19,030 --> 00:12:20,790
It's on Beijiang Road in the northeast.

187
00:12:20,790 --> 00:12:21,910
Keep an eye on him.

188
00:12:22,270 --> 00:12:23,870
Report any situation at once.

189
00:12:23,870 --> 00:12:24,510
Copy that.

190
00:12:24,790 --> 00:12:25,510
Stay close.

191
00:12:32,270 --> 00:12:32,910
Wan,

192
00:12:33,160 --> 00:12:34,750
is there any movement from He Wu?

193
00:12:34,750 --> 00:12:35,960
Follow my location.

194
00:12:36,360 --> 00:12:37,000
Okay.

195
00:13:04,150 --> 00:13:05,080
Boss, you...

196
00:13:21,720 --> 00:13:22,600
So,

197
00:13:23,720 --> 00:13:25,650
we're not doing business tonight?

198
00:13:25,870 --> 00:13:26,730
What business?

199
00:13:31,360 --> 00:13:32,630
You mean

200
00:13:33,510 --> 00:13:35,060
the goods at Jingang Wharf?

201
00:13:40,870 --> 00:13:42,480
All the bros here know

202
00:13:43,360 --> 00:13:45,440
a batch of goods

203
00:13:45,440 --> 00:13:47,170
will be shipped there tonight.

204
00:13:51,790 --> 00:13:53,000
Hey, this...

205
00:13:53,000 --> 00:13:54,240
This intel is fake.

206
00:14:00,510 --> 00:14:02,350
We set this up just to…

207
00:14:06,150 --> 00:14:07,390
just to kill him.

208
00:14:10,550 --> 00:14:12,200
Just to kill him!

209
00:14:24,870 --> 00:14:25,600
Hello.

210
00:14:25,600 --> 00:14:26,030
Long time no see.

211
00:14:26,030 --> 00:14:26,790
Hello.

212
00:14:30,550 --> 00:14:31,630
Leader Yao. Leader Yao.

213
00:14:31,630 --> 00:14:33,910
The first batch
of reinforcements is in place.

214
00:14:33,910 --> 00:14:34,550
Okay.

215
00:14:34,870 --> 00:14:37,080
Act only after confirming the drug deal.

216
00:14:37,080 --> 00:14:38,210
Wait for my command.

217
00:14:38,240 --> 00:14:38,870
Copy that.

218
00:14:50,940 --> 00:14:51,580
Move out.

219
00:14:54,120 --> 00:14:54,750
Freeze!

220
00:14:54,750 --> 00:14:55,300
Police!

221
00:14:55,330 --> 00:14:55,780
Stop!

222
00:14:55,800 --> 00:14:56,370
Stop!

223
00:14:57,080 --> 00:14:57,630
Stop!

224
00:14:57,870 --> 00:14:58,440
Get down!

225
00:14:58,460 --> 00:14:59,010
Stop!

226
00:15:22,080 --> 00:15:22,630
Report.

227
00:15:22,650 --> 00:15:24,140
It's all flour. No drugs.

228
00:15:31,030 --> 00:15:32,160
Something's wrong.

229
00:15:32,510 --> 00:15:34,110
Tell them to pull out, quick!

230
00:16:01,070 --> 00:16:01,980
Tell me,

231
00:16:02,320 --> 00:16:04,370
why so many police

232
00:16:04,480 --> 00:16:06,000
showed up to raid

233
00:16:07,140 --> 00:16:08,810
our cargo ship full of timber

234
00:16:08,840 --> 00:16:10,290
at Jingang Wharf?

235
00:16:10,550 --> 00:16:12,210
The police really went there?

236
00:16:13,270 --> 00:16:14,320
A lot of them.

237
00:16:14,720 --> 00:16:15,910
It seems we really

238
00:16:16,340 --> 00:16:17,600
have a mole here.

239
00:16:19,080 --> 00:16:20,080
Who could they be?

240
00:16:34,360 --> 00:16:36,360
A mole...

241
00:16:38,390 --> 00:16:39,360
A mole.

242
00:16:45,910 --> 00:16:47,970
Wan, you guys pin down He Wu first.

243
00:16:48,200 --> 00:16:49,150
Yes. Move out.

244
00:17:22,849 --> 00:17:23,650
Sniper!

245
00:17:23,680 --> 00:17:24,880
Everyone, take cover!

246
00:17:24,880 --> 00:17:25,690
Are you okay?

247
00:17:25,720 --> 00:17:26,400
I'm fine.

248
00:17:26,680 --> 00:17:27,480
I can hold on.

249
00:17:34,680 --> 00:17:35,480
It's the cops.

250
00:17:35,830 --> 00:17:36,480
Boss.

251
00:17:36,480 --> 00:17:37,720
Is there another exit?

252
00:17:37,720 --> 00:17:38,480
Follow me.

253
00:17:41,980 --> 00:17:42,610
Let's go.

254
00:17:50,530 --> 00:17:51,530
We are ambushed.

255
00:17:51,650 --> 00:17:53,910
Requesting backup. Requesting backup.

256
00:17:58,590 --> 00:17:59,240
Senior,

257
00:17:59,690 --> 00:18:00,970
they came prepared.

258
00:18:01,240 --> 00:18:02,440
It's not an easy task.

259
00:18:03,110 --> 00:18:03,960
Stay here.

260
00:18:03,960 --> 00:18:04,880
Protect yourself.

261
00:18:04,880 --> 00:18:05,780
Where are you going?

262
00:18:05,780 --> 00:18:07,070
I'm going to draw him out.

263
00:18:07,070 --> 00:18:07,720
No.

264
00:18:07,770 --> 00:18:08,900
It's too dangerous!

265
00:18:13,270 --> 00:18:13,920
Senior.

266
00:18:28,870 --> 00:18:30,020
Interesting.

267
00:18:32,790 --> 00:18:33,720
Here, quick!

268
00:18:41,680 --> 00:18:42,350
Quick!

269
00:20:28,360 --> 00:20:29,270
Interesting.

270
00:20:32,620 --> 00:20:33,980
Very interesting.

271
00:21:20,200 --> 00:21:20,920
Go!

272
00:21:20,920 --> 00:21:22,720
Old Scorpion is waiting for you.

273
00:21:40,880 --> 00:21:41,640
Hurry.

274
00:21:58,110 --> 00:21:59,720
If you want to live,

275
00:22:00,740 --> 00:22:02,270
I suggest you stop chasing.

276
00:22:04,270 --> 00:22:05,750
You might as well shoot me.

277
00:22:06,850 --> 00:22:07,860
Jiang Cheng.

278
00:22:26,640 --> 00:22:27,590
Why are you here?

279
00:22:28,200 --> 00:22:29,270
Don't touch me!

280
00:22:29,960 --> 00:22:30,920
Stop chasing.

281
00:22:34,080 --> 00:22:35,270
Don't touch me.

282
00:22:44,880 --> 00:22:46,540
I should be the one asking you.

283
00:22:47,240 --> 00:22:48,550
Why are you here?

284
00:22:50,160 --> 00:22:51,500
Why is it you?

285
00:22:52,240 --> 00:22:53,070
Jiang Cheng.

286
00:22:55,200 --> 00:22:57,400
Are you really dealing drugs with them?

287
00:22:58,990 --> 00:23:00,830
Why are you doing this? Answer me.

288
00:23:00,830 --> 00:23:02,830
Stop talking. Stop talking about it.

289
00:23:02,830 --> 00:23:03,920
Why?

290
00:23:04,570 --> 00:23:05,810
Do you know

291
00:23:05,830 --> 00:23:07,480
the man you just let go

292
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:09,240
was?

293
00:23:09,680 --> 00:23:11,960
Do you know they kill police officers?

294
00:23:12,480 --> 00:23:13,590
Do you know

295
00:23:13,590 --> 00:23:15,000
the people you're dealing drugs with

296
00:23:15,000 --> 00:23:16,110
killed Chuan?

297
00:23:19,400 --> 00:23:22,160
Do you know they killed Chuan?

298
00:23:22,160 --> 00:23:23,790
They killed Chuan!

299
00:23:24,350 --> 00:23:26,030
Do you know that?

300
00:23:35,270 --> 00:23:36,530
I know.

301
00:23:59,240 --> 00:23:59,790
Zhou Jin,

302
00:24:00,920 --> 00:24:01,650
are you okay?

303
00:24:02,160 --> 00:24:02,760
Hansheng,

304
00:24:04,290 --> 00:24:05,350
how did you find me?

305
00:24:07,110 --> 00:24:07,710
I'm sorry.

306
00:24:07,790 --> 00:24:08,590
I'm late.

307
00:24:31,070 --> 00:24:32,590
Did Chuan let you down,

308
00:24:33,360 --> 00:24:34,750
or did I let you down?

309
00:24:43,000 --> 00:24:43,750
Do you know

310
00:24:43,750 --> 00:24:45,440
the man you just let go

311
00:24:45,440 --> 00:24:46,840
killed police officers?

312
00:24:47,280 --> 00:24:48,200
Do you know

313
00:24:48,200 --> 00:24:49,480
the people you're dealing drugs with

314
00:24:49,480 --> 00:24:50,720
killed Chuan?

315
00:25:59,720 --> 00:26:00,830
The tetanus shot hurts a bit.

316
00:26:00,830 --> 00:26:02,230
Bear with it for a moment.

317
00:26:11,270 --> 00:26:12,400
Ready for stitches.

318
00:27:05,790 --> 00:27:07,440
Officer Jiang!

319
00:27:27,400 --> 00:27:29,030
Officer Jiang!

320
00:27:31,110 --> 00:27:32,150
Killing people—

321
00:27:32,920 --> 00:27:33,780
Is it exciting?

322
00:27:33,960 --> 00:27:36,510
Officer Jiang has deep insights

323
00:27:36,510 --> 00:27:38,160
in the field of psychology.

324
00:27:38,160 --> 00:27:39,440
Can't you understand my work?

325
00:27:39,440 --> 00:27:40,420
There's no other way.

326
00:27:40,420 --> 00:27:41,480
If I don't kill them,

327
00:27:41,480 --> 00:27:42,480
I can't calm down.

328
00:27:42,640 --> 00:27:43,440
Just like you!

329
00:27:43,510 --> 00:27:44,200
Officer Jiang.

330
00:27:44,200 --> 00:27:44,920
Right now,

331
00:27:45,070 --> 00:27:47,310
do you want to kill me?

332
00:27:47,790 --> 00:27:48,200
Kill me!

333
00:27:48,200 --> 00:27:48,790
Officer Jiang!

334
00:27:48,790 --> 00:27:49,480
Come on.

335
00:27:49,480 --> 00:27:50,640
Don't suppress your desires!

336
00:27:50,640 --> 00:27:51,550
Kill me.

337
00:27:51,640 --> 00:27:52,200
Kill me.

338
00:27:52,270 --> 00:27:53,350
Kill me.

339
00:27:53,350 --> 00:27:54,790
For the girl you love,

340
00:27:54,790 --> 00:27:56,070
kill me!

341
00:28:13,310 --> 00:28:14,880
Watch your diet recently.

342
00:28:15,070 --> 00:28:16,030
Don't make big movements,

343
00:28:16,030 --> 00:28:17,630
so you don't tear your wound.

344
00:28:18,110 --> 00:28:19,240
Change the dressing in 3 days,

345
00:28:19,240 --> 00:28:21,100
and remove the stitches in 7 days.

346
00:28:21,110 --> 00:28:21,680
Got it?

347
00:28:22,440 --> 00:28:23,200
Thank you.

348
00:28:23,400 --> 00:28:24,330
You're welcome.

349
00:28:24,640 --> 00:28:26,710
Your husband went to the pharmacy
to get your medicine.

350
00:28:26,710 --> 00:28:28,110
You can wait for him here.

351
00:28:41,920 --> 00:28:42,640
Mentor.

352
00:28:42,750 --> 00:28:43,590
What is it?

353
00:28:43,720 --> 00:28:44,590
Are you alone?

354
00:28:46,240 --> 00:28:46,920
Go ahead.

355
00:28:47,680 --> 00:28:49,280
Has Leader Yao been rescued?

356
00:28:54,880 --> 00:28:56,210
We're still searching.

357
00:28:56,630 --> 00:28:59,160
How could you go looking
for the sniper alone?

358
00:28:59,510 --> 00:29:01,230
What if you didn't make it back?

359
00:29:01,230 --> 00:29:02,960
It was Jiang Cheng who saved me.

360
00:29:04,240 --> 00:29:04,720
What?

361
00:29:05,350 --> 00:29:07,160
He escorted the sniper away,

362
00:29:07,480 --> 00:29:09,000
which basically saved me.

363
00:29:09,000 --> 00:29:09,640
Chief Tan!

364
00:29:12,440 --> 00:29:13,200
Okay, I got it.

365
00:29:13,200 --> 00:29:14,880
Chief Tan, it's a call
from the Provincial Bureau.

366
00:29:14,880 --> 00:29:15,680
Write a report first.

367
00:29:15,680 --> 00:29:16,940
I'll talk to you later.

368
00:29:18,270 --> 00:29:18,750
Okay.

369
00:29:32,510 --> 00:29:33,040
Zhou Jin.

370
00:29:35,820 --> 00:29:36,480
How are you?

371
00:29:37,070 --> 00:29:38,130
Does it still hurt?

372
00:29:41,400 --> 00:29:41,930
I'm fine.

373
00:30:20,460 --> 00:30:22,260
Do you have something to tell me?

374
00:30:27,830 --> 00:30:28,920
I'm a little tired.

375
00:30:59,950 --> 00:31:00,710
Zhou Jin.

376
00:31:02,750 --> 00:31:04,210
Don't do this again, okay?

377
00:31:05,310 --> 00:31:07,060
Before you do anything dangerous,

378
00:31:07,060 --> 00:31:08,010
think of me.

379
00:31:12,510 --> 00:31:13,440
Okay.

380
00:31:26,200 --> 00:31:26,880
By the way,

381
00:31:28,830 --> 00:31:30,110
how did you find me?

382
00:31:30,830 --> 00:31:32,030
Why are you able

383
00:31:33,060 --> 00:31:34,930
to arrive so quickly every time?

384
00:31:36,310 --> 00:31:38,170
Because you always make me worry.

385
00:31:38,480 --> 00:31:39,700
Hurry up and brush your teeth.

386
00:31:39,700 --> 00:31:40,590
Then, go to bed.

387
00:31:40,990 --> 00:31:41,990
You must be tired.

388
00:32:08,920 --> 00:32:09,550
Hansheng.

389
00:32:10,920 --> 00:32:13,250
5 years ago, I let you
and your master down,

390
00:32:13,510 --> 00:32:14,440
especially you.

391
00:32:15,430 --> 00:32:16,640
I am deeply sorry.

392
00:32:17,610 --> 00:32:19,090
If it really is a trap,

393
00:32:19,750 --> 00:32:21,080
I will follow your path.

394
00:32:21,900 --> 00:32:23,010
Dead or alive,

395
00:32:23,250 --> 00:32:24,710
I'll bring back the clues.

396
00:32:26,180 --> 00:32:27,070
You and Zhou Jin

397
00:32:28,160 --> 00:32:29,220
must never give up.

398
00:32:39,060 --> 00:32:39,790
Prof.

399
00:32:40,730 --> 00:32:41,730
I was wrong.

400
00:32:42,640 --> 00:32:44,270
Qi Yan is not dead.

401
00:32:45,920 --> 00:32:47,600
Now, Leader Yao is in trouble.

402
00:32:59,410 --> 00:33:00,560
I heard about it.

403
00:33:01,520 --> 00:33:02,840
Don't overthink it.

404
00:33:03,880 --> 00:33:05,270
Be careful.

405
00:33:37,790 --> 00:33:38,520
Jiang Cheng.

406
00:33:42,680 --> 00:33:43,410
Jiang Cheng.

407
00:34:12,800 --> 00:34:14,550
Pass it! Pass it!

408
00:34:14,670 --> 00:34:16,510
Pass the ball!

409
00:34:16,510 --> 00:34:18,570
Why dribble if you can't get past him?

410
00:34:22,440 --> 00:34:23,280
Jin.

411
00:34:29,179 --> 00:34:30,570
Why are you here?

412
00:34:35,070 --> 00:34:35,800
I'm back,

413
00:34:35,949 --> 00:34:36,510
Jin.

414
00:34:44,710 --> 00:34:45,310
Jin.

415
00:34:46,850 --> 00:34:47,850
It was my fault.

416
00:34:48,920 --> 00:34:50,070
Don't cry anymore.

417
00:34:55,510 --> 00:34:56,239
Jiang Cheng!

418
00:34:57,510 --> 00:34:58,510
Jiang Cheng!

419
00:35:07,380 --> 00:35:08,170
Jiang Cheng.

420
00:35:09,910 --> 00:35:10,720
Jiang Cheng.

421
00:35:19,030 --> 00:35:20,430
Did you have a nightmare?

422
00:35:22,730 --> 00:35:23,480
I'm fine.

423
00:35:30,490 --> 00:35:31,890
What did you dream about?

424
00:35:36,230 --> 00:35:37,110
Nothing.

425
00:35:49,590 --> 00:35:50,520
Go back to sleep.

426
00:36:51,640 --> 00:36:52,930
Officer Jiang,

427
00:36:54,230 --> 00:36:55,280
does your girl

428
00:36:56,390 --> 00:36:58,020
really care about you?

429
00:38:13,040 --> 00:38:14,440
Why aren't you sleeping?

430
00:38:20,280 --> 00:38:21,110
I saw

431
00:38:24,340 --> 00:38:25,530
Jiang Cheng today.

432
00:38:34,760 --> 00:38:36,760
I almost got killed

433
00:38:39,690 --> 00:38:40,960
chasing that sniper.

434
00:38:43,960 --> 00:38:45,690
It was Jiang Cheng who saved me.

435
00:39:12,230 --> 00:39:14,400
Leader Yao received a reliable tip

436
00:39:14,750 --> 00:39:16,680
that there will be a major drug deal

437
00:39:16,930 --> 00:39:18,330
at Jingang Wharf today.

438
00:39:19,000 --> 00:39:19,960
So Leader Yao

439
00:39:20,190 --> 00:39:22,320
will personally lead a team there
to make the arrest.

440
00:39:22,320 --> 00:39:24,120
However, before your next move,

441
00:39:24,780 --> 00:39:25,550
I hope

442
00:39:26,190 --> 00:39:27,650
you can look into someone.

443
00:39:28,070 --> 00:39:28,480
Who?

444
00:39:29,190 --> 00:39:29,920
Jiang Cheng.

445
00:39:30,710 --> 00:39:31,280
Why?

446
00:39:33,030 --> 00:39:35,360
Aren't you supposed to ask
who he is first?

447
00:39:54,770 --> 00:39:56,120
Attention, all units.

448
00:39:56,190 --> 00:39:58,800
Maintain current duty status for 42 hours.

449
00:39:59,190 --> 00:40:01,630
Increase patrol frequency at the station.

450
00:40:02,070 --> 00:40:04,670
Thoroughly investigate
every suspicious person.

451
00:40:04,670 --> 00:40:05,960
Seal off Hengyun Logistics,

452
00:40:05,960 --> 00:40:06,920
Phoenix Fire Bar,

453
00:40:06,920 --> 00:40:09,760
and other businesses
closely related to the suspects.

454
00:40:09,760 --> 00:40:12,710
Conduct a full investigation
into their connections.

455
00:40:12,710 --> 00:40:15,060
Any information related
to Comrade Yao Weihai

456
00:40:15,060 --> 00:40:16,360
must be reported immediately.

457
00:40:16,360 --> 00:40:18,150
Treat every clue seriously.

458
00:40:18,190 --> 00:40:19,250
Verify carefully.

459
00:40:44,840 --> 00:40:46,880
Their target was very clear,

460
00:40:46,880 --> 00:40:48,400
and they moved very fast.

461
00:40:48,760 --> 00:40:50,480
The tunnel was dug in advance.

462
00:40:50,550 --> 00:40:53,230
The entrance was
in the container warehouse.

463
00:40:53,440 --> 00:40:55,670
The container warehouse was just a cover.

464
00:40:55,670 --> 00:40:56,510
After the explosion,

465
00:40:56,510 --> 00:40:58,320
there was brief chaos.

466
00:40:58,590 --> 00:41:00,040
That's when Leader Yao

467
00:41:00,140 --> 00:41:01,100
was pulled into the tunnel.

468
00:41:00,240 --> 00:41:04,250
[Director Wang Pengze]

469
00:41:01,440 --> 00:41:02,920
They also left some cannon fodder

470
00:41:02,920 --> 00:41:04,320
to resist the police.

471
00:41:04,670 --> 00:41:06,840
It was actually just to buy time.

472
00:41:07,070 --> 00:41:08,390
Where does this tunnel lead?

473
00:41:08,390 --> 00:41:11,140
It leads directly
to the city's sewer system.

474
00:41:11,800 --> 00:41:12,400
By the way,

475
00:41:12,710 --> 00:41:14,190
after they left the tunnel,

476
00:41:14,190 --> 00:41:16,120
they detonated explosives twice.

477
00:41:16,480 --> 00:41:18,550
The entrance
has collapsed from the explosion.

478
00:41:18,550 --> 00:41:21,010
Our SWAT officers
were almost buried alive.

479
00:41:23,320 --> 00:41:25,150
Leader Yao has been missing

480
00:41:25,360 --> 00:41:26,840
for more than 48 hours.

481
00:41:27,090 --> 00:41:28,180
If this

482
00:41:28,280 --> 00:41:29,030
really is

483
00:41:29,440 --> 00:41:31,000
a trap set by Qi Yan,

484
00:41:31,930 --> 00:41:34,000
the consequences could be catastrophic.

485
00:41:34,000 --> 00:41:35,190
When Jiang Hansheng told me

486
00:41:35,190 --> 00:41:37,850
that there was a fifth person
in this warehouse,

487
00:41:38,190 --> 00:41:39,480
I got chills, too.

488
00:41:41,710 --> 00:41:42,550
It seems they are

489
00:41:42,550 --> 00:41:45,150
getting revenge
for what happened 5 years ago.

490
00:41:45,190 --> 00:41:46,050
Director Wang.

491
00:41:46,190 --> 00:41:48,120
How is your progress in Huaiguang?

492
00:41:48,820 --> 00:41:50,340
Qi Yan

493
00:41:50,770 --> 00:41:52,430
is quite a mysterious figure.

494
00:41:53,110 --> 00:41:54,110
I need

495
00:41:55,280 --> 00:41:56,800
to sort this whole thing out
from the beginning

496
00:41:56,800 --> 00:41:58,710
based on the new clues we have now.

497
00:41:59,550 --> 00:42:01,010
The top priority right now

498
00:42:01,040 --> 00:42:03,200
is to find Yao

499
00:42:03,230 --> 00:42:04,560
and the undercover cop.

500
00:42:04,800 --> 00:42:05,280
Okay.

501
00:42:05,840 --> 00:42:06,570
Don't worry,

502
00:42:06,630 --> 00:42:08,430
we will definitely try our best.

503
00:42:08,910 --> 00:42:09,510
Right now,

504
00:42:09,740 --> 00:42:11,000
you're carrying a heavy burden.

505
00:42:11,000 --> 00:42:11,960
You must hold on.

506
00:42:12,110 --> 00:42:12,710
Okay.

507
00:42:13,110 --> 00:42:13,970
Director Wang,

508
00:42:14,030 --> 00:42:15,880
if there is nothing else,
we'll leave it at that.

509
00:42:15,880 --> 00:42:17,110
If there is any new situation,

510
00:42:17,110 --> 00:42:18,970
I will report to you immediately.

511
00:42:19,070 --> 00:42:19,710
And,

512
00:42:19,880 --> 00:42:20,960
emphasize it to Jiang Hansheng

513
00:42:20,960 --> 00:42:22,090
and that little girl

514
00:42:22,400 --> 00:42:23,480
once again,

515
00:42:23,480 --> 00:42:25,760
make sure they are extra careful.

516
00:42:25,800 --> 00:42:26,660
Did you hear me?

517
00:42:27,110 --> 00:42:27,710
Okay.

518
00:42:28,070 --> 00:42:29,600
Zhou Jin is right next to me.

519
00:42:29,630 --> 00:42:30,400
Don't worry.

520
00:42:30,570 --> 00:42:31,880
Okay, let's keep in touch.

521
00:42:31,880 --> 00:42:32,510
Goodbye.

522
00:42:39,150 --> 00:42:41,210
Didn't you ask what the situation is?

523
00:42:41,550 --> 00:42:43,350
This is the situation right now.

524
00:42:44,590 --> 00:42:45,990
What did Director Wang just say

525
00:42:45,990 --> 00:42:47,280
about Leader Yao

526
00:42:47,680 --> 00:42:49,010
and the undercover cop?

527
00:42:50,000 --> 00:42:51,730
Before the Jingang operation,

528
00:42:51,880 --> 00:42:53,840
Leader Yao once told me the truth.

529
00:42:54,840 --> 00:42:57,170
Right now, there's an undercover officer

530
00:42:57,230 --> 00:42:59,030
inside Old Scorpion's
criminal organization.

531
00:42:59,030 --> 00:43:00,510
His code name is Cangfeng.

532
00:43:01,280 --> 00:43:03,480
He had been in one-way contact with him.

533
00:43:04,710 --> 00:43:05,510
Cangfeng?
